      <physical-reality>
        <reasoning>Three weeks after the battle the facility has been actively rebuilt and repurposed by the plant community. The common area (where the narrator stands) is physically transformed: a bowl‑shaped depression in the floor now functions as a resonance chamber connected to Runner’s underground network; Velvet’s growth has been shaped into ergonomic seating, alcoves, and mossed sleeping areas; Scout-sized alcoves in a wall contain curated objects; Remedy has a functioning chemistry/workbench producing aromatic/environmental compounds; Holloway provides bioluminescent lighting and moves between work sites; Florence’s wheeled platform is present and mobile. The underground network has been extended beyond transport/communication into acoustic and connective architecture with planned connection points into Velvet’s spaces. Eastern sections are reported structurally complete; many formerly damaged areas (at least all inhabited/repaired communal spaces) show cleared debris and made‑safe surfaces and are comfortable enough for rest and testing. The central core no longer contains the hostile command node (it was removed earlier and remains outside the perimeter) and appears stabilized or being redesigned rather than actively occupied by hostile material; however at least one wing (the western wing) remains to be renovated—plans to start it tomorrow are in place. A communication array is active and has just detected an artificial signal of possible human origin. Environmental conditions in the occupied areas are pleasant: bioluminescent lighting, pleasant scents from Remedy’s compounds, tuned acoustics in resonance chambers, appropriate temperatures and ergonomics. Plant injuries and resource depletion from the battle have largely recovered enough for active construction and creative work, though community members are still tired from rebuilding. The scene ends with beings gathered in comfortable silence and an active, unresolved external signal detected by the communication array.</reasoning>
        <state>Three weeks after the battle, the facility’s common area and eastern sections are largely repaired and repurposed: Velvet‑grown seating, moss sleeping alcoves, and Scout‑height display alcoves line the walls; a bowl‑shaped resonance chamber in the floor links to Runner’s expanded underground network of acoustic/communication chambers; Remedy’s chemistry bench emits new aromatic/environmental compounds; Holloway’s bioluminescent lighting is installed and mobile; Florence’s wheeled platform and the core personnel (Kira, Scout, Runner, Velvet, Remedy, Holloway, Florence) are present and recuperating in the refurbished communal spaces. Debris and toxic residues appear cleared or remediated in occupied areas, though at least the western wing remains unrenovated and the facility still bears the legacy of prior structural damage elsewhere. The hostile command node removed earlier remains outside the facility perimeter. The communication array is active and has just detected an artificial (possibly human) signal. Overall atmosphere: physically comfortable, acoustically and olfactorily tuned spaces, repaired structural integrity in worked‑on sections, active underground network and building projects continuing, with a new external signal creating immediate uncertainty.</state>
      </physical-reality>
